Explanation/Notes : When loading the initial traditional notes page and the single-page app (SPA), the process is largely similar. Both involve the browser making GET requests to the server for the necessary HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files. The server responds by providing these resources, enabling the browser to render the base page.

The key difference is seen only when the user submits their "note" using the form in the SPA. We will explore this further in activity 0.6.

